<p>You’ve already seen one example from Squarespace’s homepage in this article, but if you scroll further down the site you’ll see the page is chock-full of sliders – and they all look stunning.</p>
<figure id="attachment_5018" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-5018" style="width: 780px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img src="https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/squarespace.jpg" alt="Template slider - Squarespace" width="780" height="337" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-5018" srcset="https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/squarespace.jpg 780w, https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/squarespace-300x130.jpg 300w, https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/squarespace-768x332.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-5018" class="wp-caption-text">Template slider &#8211; Squarespace</figcaption></figure>
<p>Sliders are ideal for hotel and accommodation sites like Airbnb that want to display a scrolling selection of options for users. </p>
