<p>Amazon makes liberal use of sliders to display products on its homepage. The sliders it uses have been designed so you can see a hint of the next product in the carousel. It peeks out from the right, prompting you to click on the arrow so you can see the product image and description in full.</p>
<figure id="attachment_5020" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-5020" style="width: 780px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img src="https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/amazon.jpg" alt="Product slider - Amazon" width="780" height="312" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-5020" srcset="https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/amazon.jpg 780w, https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/amazon-300x120.jpg 300w, https://smartslider3.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/amazon-768x307.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-5020" class="wp-caption-text">Product slider &#8211; Amazon</figcaption></figure>
